This is a distinctive species on account of the unusually long and slender metasoma (Fig. 
16A
), the anterior tergites of which are strongly elongate and longitudinally striate (Fig. 
16G
); the wings are narrow, antenna with 31-36 flagellomeres, basal flagellomere 2.3-2.5 times as long as wide.
